# Java tips

````
finish(): This method finishes the current activity, effectively closing the app if this is the main activity.

onBackPressed(): If your activity is part of a stack and has a parent activity, calling onBackPressed() simulates pressing the device's back button, which could navigate back to the previous activity.

Choose the option that fits your application's navigation flow. If the splash screen is your main activity, finish() might be more appropriate. If the splash screen is part of a navigation flow, and you want to go back to the previous screen, you can use onBackPressed().

````
